				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$N=11\text{,}884$\end{document}). However, for the purpose of investigating performance as a function of dataset size, we have sub-sampled the training dataset to create a series of smaller datasets. These subsets were generated by drawing random samples from the training dataset while the holdout test dataset remains unchanged. Table 5
