				\begin{document}$\theta _{\mathrm{LR}}$\end{document} and θSLR\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\theta _{\mathrm{SLR}}$\end{document}) are relatively difficult properties to regress. These post-impact properties show a strong dependence on the pre-impact rotation rate (Ω) and obliquity (θ) of the associated body. Once again, the Sobol’ indices indicate the same feature importance. For the obliquity of the LR (θLR\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
