				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$v_{\infty }$\end{document}). Where other pre-impact properties have been selected, they tend to have a physically intuitive relationship to the post-impact property. Note that PCE did not select the pre-impact azimuthal orientations, ϕtarg\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
